\end{align}$

Substituting the values of $\maroonD f$ and $\blueD v$ above, we get the object distance $u$,

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{1}{ u}&=\dfrac{1}{(\maroonD{-16\ \text{cm}})}-\dfrac{1}{(\blueD{+9.6\ \text{cm}})}\\\\
&=\dfrac{6.0\ \text{cm} - (-10)\ \text{cm}}{-96\ \text{cm}^2}\\\\
&=\dfrac{\cancel{16}\ \cancel{\text{cm}}}{-\stackrel{6}{\cancel{96}}\ \text{cm}^{\cancel 2}}\\\\
\Rightarrow  u&=-6.0\ \text{cm}
\end{align}$

